children.subject: I did all three in the same semester; i felt like I was spending equal amounts of time on 70 and 16B. 70 psets were short but hard, 16B psets were long but medium difficulty. Think 16B was overall easier as a class.

history.content: I took all 3 last semester. I did no hw option for 70 which was a great time save but 16b psets were very difficult under Sahai and took 8-12hrs. To give context, I did this with only 16a linear algebra experience and no discrete math experience. I'd recommend taking 70 next semester if you want to do upper div CS next fall.

children.subject: I haven’t taken 16b, but from what I gather it’s easier than 70 but more time consuming (for most people.) If the material in 70 comes naturally to you, it can end up being a very chill class, especially if you go with the test only option. If it doesn’t come naturally to you at all, 70 could end up taking more time than 16b.
